    "category_validation": {
      "expected_category": "mpmc_pub_sub",
      "validated": true,
      "evidence_note": "Repo-wide validation at the pinned commit supports the mpmc_pub_sub category. tokio::sync::broadcast is central to the daemon: DaemonHandle emits DaemonEvent values and components/services subscribe to the event bus, including the main daemon event loop and history tailing. tokio::sync::mpsc appears in localized roles: daemon sync commands, gRPC streaming response adapters, and interactive script stdin/exit channels. tokio::sync::oneshot appears only as a script-execution stop signal for a stdin forwarding task. I did not find competing-consumer worker-pool style channel usage outside tests/benchmarks."
    }
